## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of finance in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Finance is the bounded formal structure
through which balances,
settlement,
obligations,
claims,
reserves,
and accounting consequences
become meaningful.

Finance is narrower and more formal than economy.
Economy expresses value circulation;
finance expresses formally tracked monetary or monetary-like consequence.

## architectural_position
Finance sits between:
- economic consequence
- trade and market settlement
- company and organization funds
- nation policy/tax effect
- reporting and audit reconstruction

## required_behavior
- finance identity/context must remain explicit
- balance and obligation basis must remain explicit
- current and historical finance states must remain distinguishable
- settlement and reservation must remain distinguishable

## canonical_rules
- pending settlement must not masquerade as settled balance
- reserved amounts must not masquerade as freely available amounts
- historical finance trace must remain queryable
- ambiguous finance state fails closed

## state_model
The finance domain distinguishes:
- pending finance state
- available balance state
- reserved balance state
- settled state
- disputed state
- historical finance state

## actor_boundary
- holder/controller
- operator
- reviewer
- approver
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if finance context is unclear, stop finance-sensitive action
- if balance/obligation basis is unclear, fail closed
- if settlement path is incomplete, deny finalization
- if state becomes historical, preserve settlement trace

## review_checklist
- finance context is explicit
- balance/obligation basis is explicit
- settlement model is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
